    <section>
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>2 cups all-purpose flour</li>
            <li>1/4 cup ghee or vegetable oil</li>
            <li>1/2 cup water (approximately)</li>
            <li>1 cup boiled and mashed potatoes</li>
            <li>1/2 cup peas</li>
            <li>1/4 cup chopped onions</li>
            <li>1 tsp cumin seeds</li>
            <li>1 tsp ginger-garlic paste</li>
            <li>1 tsp garam masala</li>
            <li>1 tsp coriander powder</li>
            <li>1/2 tsp turmeric powder</li>
            <li>Salt to taste</li>
            <li>Oil for frying</li>
        </ul>
    </section>



    <section>
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>In a mixing bowl, combine the all-purpose flour and ghee. Gradually add water and knead into a smooth dough. Let it rest for 30 minutes.</li>
            <li>In a pan, heat oil and add cumin seeds. Once they splutter, add chopped onions and sauté until golden brown.</li>
            <li>Add ginger-garlic paste and sauté for a minute. Add peas, mashed potatoes, and all the spices. Mix well and cook for 5-7 minutes.</li>
            <li>Divide the dough into small balls. Roll each ball into a thin disc.</li>
            <li>Cut each disc in half to form two semi-circles. Fold each semi-circle to form a cone, sealing the edges with water.</li>
            <li>Fill each cone with the potato mixture and seal the open edge to form a triangular shape.</li>
            <li>Heat oil in a pan and deep-fry the samosas until golden brown and crispy.</li>
            <li>Remove excess oil by placing the samosas on paper towels.</li>
            <li>Serve hot with mint chutney or tamarind sauce.</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

